| classification = Former {{ill|Sonsha|ja|村社}}
| established = {{ill|1125|ja|1125年}} ({{ill|Tenji 2|ja|天治2年}})
| architecture = Three-bay {{ill|Nagare-zukuri|ja|流造}} with decorative Chidori gable and Karahafu porch
| festivals = Hatsuo Grand Festival (late {{ill|March|ja|3月}}), Shinjo-sai (November 23)
}}

'''Kanmuri Inari Shrine''' (冠稲荷神社) is a {{ill|Shinto shrine|ja|神社}} located in {{ill|Hosoya|ja|細谷町}}, Ota City, Gunma Prefecture. It is regarded as one of the {{ill|Seven Great Inari Shrines|ja|日本七社}}.<ref>{{Cite web|ja|title=冠稲荷神社と日本七社|url=https://kanmuri.com/ka/jinjanituite/kannmuri_nanansya/|publisher=Kanmuri Inari Shrine|accessdate=2024-11-26}}</ref> Historically, the shrine was revered as a deity of sericulture. It is classified as a former {{ill|Sonsha|ja|村社}} under Japan's modern shrine ranking system.{{Sfn|Ota City|1985|pp=42,57-58}}

== Enshrined Deities ==

* {{ill|Uka-no-Mitama-no-Kami|ja|宇迦御魂神}}
* {{ill|Ōnamuchi-no-Mikoto|ja|大穴牟遅神}}
* {{ill|Ōta-no-Kami|ja|太田神}}
* {{ill|Ōmiyahime-no-Mikoto|ja|大宮能売神}}
* {{ill|Ukemochi|ja|保食命}}
* {{ill|Sukunabikona-no-Kami|ja|少彦名神}}
* {{ill|Emperor Ōjin|ja|品陀和気神}}
* {{ill|Kushinadahime|ja|菊理日売神}}
* {{ill|Ichikishimahime-no-Mikoto|ja|市杵島毘売神}}
* {{ill|Ōmononushi-no-Kami|ja|大物主神}}
* {{ill|Sugawara no Michizane|ja|菅原道眞公}}
* {{ill|Takeminakata|ja|建御名方神}}
* {{ill|Susanoo|ja|素盞鳴神}}
* {{ill|Kushinadahime|ja|奇稲田比賣神}}
* {{ill|Amaterasu|ja|天照大御神}}
* {{ill|Haraedo-no-Ōkami|ja|祓戸四神}}
* {{ill|Yakushi Nyorai|ja|薬師菩薩明神}}

== Overview ==

The shrine is said to have been founded in {{ill|1125|ja|1125年}} ({{ill|Tenji 2|ja|天治2年}}) by {{ill|Minamoto no Yoshikuni|ja|源義国}}.{{Sfn|Gunma Cultural Affairs Department|2022|pp=350-354}}

In {{ill|1174|ja|1174年}} ({{ill|Jōan 4|ja|承安4年}}), {{ill|Minamoto no Yoshitsune|ja|源義経}} is believed to have enshrined a divided spirit from {{ill|Fushimi Inari Taisha|ja|伏見稲荷大社}} in his crown upon learning of the shrine's Minamoto lineage, thus bestowing its name.{{Sfn|Gunma Cultural Affairs Department|2022|pp=350-354}}{{Sfn|Ota City|1985|pp=681-682}}

In {{ill|1333|ja|1333年}} ({{ill|Genkō 3|ja|元弘3年}}), {{ill|Nitta Yoshisada|ja|新田義貞}} prayed for victory at the shrine before launching his campaign. After his victory, he dedicated a ceremonial lion offering and planted fragrant {{ill|Kinmokusei|ja|キンモクセイ}} trees. He also donated land to the shrine.{{Sfn|Gunma Cultural Affairs Department|2022|pp=350-354}}

The shrine is famous for its {{ill|Boke (Chaenomeles)|ja|ボケ}} flowers, designated as a natural monument by Gunma Prefecture.

== Grounds ==

<gallery>
File:Kanmuri-inari-jinja Kinoe-o-torii.jpg|Kinoe Grand Torii
File:Kanmuri-inari-jinja honden.jpg|Main Hall
File:Kanmuri-inari-jinja Byakko-sha.jpg|Inari White Fox Shrine
File:Kanmuri-inari-jinja shamusho.jpg|Shrine Office
File:Kanmuri-inari-jinja homotsuden.jpg|Treasure Hall
</gallery>

== Cultural Properties ==

=== Gunma Prefectural Cultural Properties ===

'''Important Cultural Properties:'''
* Main Hall and Seitengū Shrine (Designated September 26, 1972)<ref>{{Cite web|ja|title=冠稲荷神社の本殿並びに聖天宮|url=https://www.city.ota.gunma.jp/page/4399.html|publisher=Ota City|accessdate=2024-08-23}}</ref>
** Main Hall: Built in {{ill|1767|ja|享保7年}}, featuring three-bay {{ill|Nagare-zukuri|ja|流造}} with Chidori gable and Karahafu porch.
** Seitengū Shrine: Four-sided {{ill|Irimoya-zukuri|ja|入母屋造}} with Karahafu roof, built in {{ill|1857|ja|安政4年}}.{{Sfn|Gunma Cultural Affairs Department|2022|pp=350-354}}<ref name=":0">{{Cite web|ja|title=冠稲荷神社を県重文に答申|url=https://www.jomo-news.co.jp/articles/-/507830|publisher=Jomo Shimbun|accessdate=2024-08-02}}</ref>

'''Natural Monuments:'''
* {{ill|Boke (Chaenomeles)|ja|ボケ}} Trees (Designated January 14, 1955)<ref>{{Cite web|ja|title=冠稲荷のボケ|url=https://www.city.ota.gunma.jp/page/4397.html|publisher=Ota City|accessdate=2024-08-23}}</ref>
** Estimated to be 300–400 years old, forming dense clusters over a semicircular area. Flowers bloom in mid-March to early April.

=== Ota City Designated Cultural Properties ===

'''Intangible Cultural Properties:'''
* Hosoya Kanmuri Inari Lion Dance (Designated March 25, 1994)<ref>{{Cite web|ja|title=細谷冠稲荷の獅子舞|url=https://www.city.ota.gunma.jp/page/4496.html|publisher=Ota City|accessdate=2024-08-23}}</ref>
** Associated with Nitta Yoshisada's ceremonial lion offering. Performed during the {{ill|Hatsuo|ja|初午}} Grand Festival.

== Access ==

=== By Car ===
* Located along {{ill|National Route 354|ja|国道354号}} Ota Bypass
* Approx. 40 minutes from {{ill|Tatebayashi IC|ja|館林インターチェンジ}} (Tohoku Expressway)
* Approx. 30 minutes from {{ill|Hanazono IC|ja|花園インターチェンジ}} (Kan-Etsu Expressway)
* Approx. 20 minutes from {{ill|Isesaki IC|ja|伊勢崎インターチェンジ}} (Kita-Kanto Expressway)

=== By Train ===
* {{ill|Tobu Isesaki Line|ja|東武伊勢崎線}}:
** 15 minutes by taxi from {{ill|Ota Station (Gunma)|ja|太田駅}}
** 20 minutes on foot from {{ill|Hosoya Station|ja|細谷駅}}

== Nearby Attractions ==
* {{ill|Sawano Elementary School|ja|太田市立沢野小学校}}
* National Historic Site: {{ill|Takayama Hikokurō Residence and Tomb|ja|高山彦九郎宅跡附遺髪塚}}

== References ==
{{Reflist|2}}

== External Links ==
* {{Official website|http://www.kanmuri.com|Kanmuri Inari Shrine}}

