'''Kanmuri Inari Shrine''' (冠稲荷神社) is a {{ill|Shinto shrine|ja|神社}} located in {{ill|Hosoya|ja|細谷町}}, Ota City, Gunma Prefecture. It is regarded as one of the {{ill|Seven Great Inari Shrines|ja|日本七社}}.<ref>{{Cite web|ja|title=冠稲荷神社と日本七社|url=https://kanmuri.com/ka/jinjanituite/kannmuri_nanansya/|publisher=Kanmuri Inari Shrine|accessdate=2024-11-26}}</ref> Historically, the shrine was revered as a deity of sericulture. It is classified as a former {{ill|Sonsha|ja|村社}} under Japan's modern shrine ranking system.{{Sfn|Ota City|1985|pp=42,57-58}}

== Enshrined Deities ==

* {{ill|Uka-no-Mitama-no-Kami|ja|宇迦御魂神}}
* {{ill|Ōnamuchi-no-Mikoto|ja|大穴牟遅神}}
* {{ill|Ōta-no-Kami|ja|太田神}}
* {{ill|Ōmiyahime-no-Mikoto|ja|大宮能売神}}
* {{ill|Ukemochi|ja|保食命}}
* {{ill|Sukunabikona-no-Kami|ja|少彦名神}}
* {{ill|Emperor Ōjin|ja|品陀和気神}}
* {{ill|Kushinadahime|ja|菊理日売神}}
* {{ill|Ichikishimahime-no-Mikoto|ja|市杵島毘売神}}
* {{ill|Ōmononushi-no-Kami|ja|大物主神}}
* {{ill|Sugawara no Michizane|ja|菅原道眞公}}
* {{ill|Takeminakata|ja|建御名方神}}
* {{ill|Susanoo|ja|素盞鳴神}}
* {{ill|Kushinadahime|ja|奇稲田比賣神}}
* {{ill|Amaterasu|ja|天照大御神}}
* {{ill|Haraedo-no-Ōkami|ja|祓戸四神}}
* {{ill|Yakushi Nyorai|ja|薬師菩薩明神}}

== Overview ==

The shrine is said to have been founded in {{ill|1125|ja|1125年}} ({{ill|Tenji 2|ja|天治2年}}) by {{ill|Minamoto no Yoshikuni|ja|源義国}}.{{Sfn|Gunma Cultural Affairs Department|2022|pp=350-354}}

In {{ill|1174|ja|1174年}} ({{ill|Jōan 4|ja|承安4年}}), {{ill|Minamoto no Yoshitsune|ja|源義経}} is believed to have enshrined a divided spirit from {{ill|Fushimi Inari Taisha|ja|伏見稲荷大社}} in his crown upon learning of the shrine's Minamoto lineage, thus bestowing its name.{{Sfn|Gunma Cultural Affairs Department|2022|pp=350-354}}{{Sfn|Ota City|1985|pp=681-682}}

In {{ill|1333|ja|1333年}} ({{ill|Genkō 3|ja|元弘3年}}), {{ill|Nitta Yoshisada|ja|新田義貞}} prayed for victory at the shrine before launching his campaign. After his victory, he dedicated a ceremonial lion offering and planted fragrant {{ill|Kinmokusei|ja|キンモクセイ}} trees. He also donated land to the shrine.{{Sfn|Gunma Cultural Affairs Department|2022|pp=350-354}}

The shrine is famous for its {{ill|Boke (Chaenomeles)|ja|ボケ}} flowers, designated as a natural monument by Gunma Prefecture.

