''' Main Hall: Built in {{ill|1767|ja|享保7th year|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, featuring three-bay {{ill|Nagare-zukuri|ja|流造|qq=draft|qq=draft}} with Chidori gable and Karahafu porch.
''' Seitengū Shrine: Four-sided {{ill|Irimoya-zukuri|ja|入母屋造|qq=draft|qq=draft}} with Karahafu roof, built in {{ill|1857|ja|安政4th year|qq=draft|qq=draft}}.{{Sfn|Gunma Cultural Affairs Department|2022|pp=350-354}}<ref name=":0">{{Cite web|ja|title=冠稲荷神社を県重文に答申|url=https://www.jomo-news.co.jp/articles/-/507830|publisher=Jomo Shimbun|accessdate=2024-08-02}}</ref>

'''Natural Monuments:'''
* {{ill|Boke (Chaenomeles)|ja|ボケ|qq=draft|qq=draft}} Trees (Designated January 14, 1955)<ref>{{Cite web|ja|title=冠稲荷のボケ|url=https://www.city.ota.gunma.jp/page/4397.html|publisher=Ota City|accessdate=2024-08-23}}</ref>
''' Estimated to be 300–400 years old, forming dense clusters over a semicircular area. Flowers bloom in mid-March to early April.

=== Ota City Designated Cultural Properties ===

'''Intangible Cultural Properties:'''
* Hosoya Kanmuri Inari Lion Dance (Designated March 25, 1994)<ref>{{Cite web|ja|title=細谷冠稲荷の獅子舞|url=https://www.city.ota.gunma.jp/page/4496.html|publisher=Ota City|accessdate=2024-08-23}}</ref>
''' Associated with Nitta Yoshisada's ceremonial lion offering. Performed during the {{ill|Hatsuo|ja|初午|qq=draft|qq=draft}} Grand Festival.

