== Overview ==

The shrine is said to have been founded in {{ill|1125|ja|1125th year|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/1125|qq=}} ({{ill|Tenji 2|ja|天治2nd year|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Tenji 2|qq=}}) by {{ill|Minamoto no Yoshikuni|ja|源義国|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Minamoto no Yoshikuni|qq=}}.{{Sfn|Gunma Cultural Affairs Department|2022|pp=350-354}}

In {{ill|1174|ja|1174th year|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/1174|qq=}} ({{ill|Jōan 4|ja|承安4th year|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Jōan 4|qq=}}), {{ill|Minamoto no Yoshitsune|ja|源義経|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Minamoto no Yoshitsune|qq=}} is believed to have enshrined a divided spirit from {{ill|Fushimi Inari Taisha|ja|伏見稲荷大社|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Fushimi Inari Taisha|qq=}} in his crown upon learning of the shrine's Minamoto lineage, thus bestowing its name.{{Sfn|Gunma Cultural Affairs Department|2022|pp=350-354}}{{Sfn|Ota City|1985|pp=681-682}}

In {{ill|1333|ja|1333rd year|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/1333|qq=}} ({{ill|Genkō 3|ja|元弘3rd year|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Genkō 3|qq=}}), {{ill|Nitta Yoshisada|ja|新田義貞|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Nitta Yoshisada|qq=}} prayed for victory at the shrine before launching his campaign. After his victory, he dedicated a ceremonial lion offering and planted fragrant {{ill|Kinmokusei|ja|キンモクセイ|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kinmokusei|qq=}} trees. He also donated land to the shrine.{{Sfn|Gunma Cultural Affairs Department|2022|pp=350-354}}

The shrine is famous for its {{ill|Boke (Chaenomeles)|ja|ボケ|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Boke (Chaenomeles)|qq=}} flowers, designated as a natural monument by Gunma Prefecture.

