'''Kanmuri Inari Shrine''' (冠稲荷神社) is a {{ill|Shinto shrine|ja|神社|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Shinto shrine|qq=}} located in {{ill|Hosoya|ja|細谷町|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Hosoya|qq=}}, Ota City, Gunma Prefecture. It is regarded as one of the {{ill|Seven Great Inari Shrines|ja|日本七社|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Seven Great Inari Shrines|qq=}}.<ref>{{Cite web|ja|title=冠稲荷神社と日本七社|url=https://kanmuri.com/ka/jinjanituite/kannmuri_nanansya/|publisher=Kanmuri Inari Shrine|accessdate=2024-11-26}}</ref> Historically, the shrine was revered as a deity of sericulture. It is classified as a former {{ill|Sonsha|ja|村社|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Sonsha|qq=}} under Japan's modern shrine Ranking system.{{Sfn|Ota City|1985|pp=42,57-58}}

== Enshrined Deities ==

* {{ill|Ukanomitama|lt=Uka-no-Mitama-no-Kami|ja|宇迦御魂神|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ukanomitama|qq=}}
* {{ill|Ōnamuchi-no-Mikoto|ja|大穴牟遅神|1=Ōkuninushi|lt=Ōnamuchi|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ōnamuchi-no-Mikoto|13=User:Immanuelle/Ōkuninushi|qq=}}
* {{ill|Ōta-no-Mikoto|lt=Ōta-no-Mikoto|lt=Ōta-no-Kami|ja|太田神|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ōta-no-Kami|qq=}}
* {{ill|Ōmiya-no-Me|lt=Ōmiya-no-Me|lt=Ōmiyahime-no-Mikoto|ja|大宮能売神|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ōmiyahime-no-Mikoto|qq=}}
* {{ill|Ukemochi|ja|保食命|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ukemochi|qq=}}
* {{ill|Sukunabikona|lt=Sukunabikona-no-Kami|ja|少彦名神|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Sukunabikona|qq=}}
* {{ill|Emperor Ōjin|ja|品陀和気神|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Emperor Ōjin|qq=}}
* {{ill|Kushinadahime|ja|菊理日売神|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kushinadahime|qq=}}
* {{ill|Ichikishima-hime-no-Mikoto|ja|市杵島毘売神|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ichikishima-hime-no-Mikoto|qq=}}
* {{ill|Ōmononushi|lt=Ōmononushi-no-Kami|ja|大物主神|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ōmononushi|qq=}}
* {{ill|Sugawara no Michizane|ja|菅原道眞公|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Sugawara no Michizane|qq=}}
* {{ill|Takeminakata|ja|建御名方神|1=Takeminakata|2=ja|3=タケミナカタ|lt=Takeminakata|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Takeminakata|qq=}}
* {{ill|Susanoo|1=Susanoo-no-Mikoto|ja|素盞鳴神|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Susanoo|13=User:Immanuelle/Susanoo-no-Mikoto|qq=}}
* {{ill|Kushinadahime|ja|奇稲田比賣神|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kushinadahime|qq=}}
* {{ill|Amaterasu|ja|天照大御神|1=Amaterasu|lt=Amaterasu Ōmikami|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Amaterasu|13=User:Immanuelle/Amaterasu|qq=}}
* {{ill|Haraedo-no-Ōkami|ja|祓戸大神|1=Haraedo no Kami|lt=Four Purification Deities|zh|祓戶大神|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Haraedo-no-Ōkami|13=User:Immanuelle/Haraedo no Kami|qq=}}
* {{ill|Yakushi Nyorai|ja|薬師菩薩明神|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Yakushi Nyorai|qq=}}

== Overview ==

The shrine is said to have been founded in {{ill|1125|ja|1125年|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/1125|qq=}} ({{ill|Tenji 2|ja|天治2nd year|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Tenji 2|qq=}}) by {{ill|Minamoto no Yoshikuni|ja|源義国|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Minamoto no Yoshikuni|qq=}}.{{Sfn|Gunma Cultural Affairs Department|2022|pp=350-354}}

In {{ill|1174|ja|1174年|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/1174|qq=}} ({{ill|Jōan 4|ja|承安4年|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Jōan 4|qq=}}), {{ill|Minamoto no Yoshitsune|ja|源義経|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Minamoto no Yoshitsune|qq=}} is believed to have enshrined a divided spirit from {{ill|Fushimi Inari Taisha|ja|伏見稲荷大社|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Fushimi Inari Taisha|qq=}} in his crown upon learning of the shrine's Minamoto lineage, thus bestowing its name.{{Sfn|Gunma Cultural Affairs Department|2022|pp=350-354}}{{Sfn|Ota City|1985|pp=681-682}}

In {{ill|1333|ja|1333rd year|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/1333|qq=}} ({{ill|Genkō 3|ja|元弘3rd year|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Genkō 3|qq=}}), {{ill|Nitta Yoshisada|ja|新田義貞|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Nitta Yoshisada|qq=}} prayed for victory at the shrine before launching his campaign. After his victory, he dedicated a ceremonial lion offering and planted fragrant {{ill|Kinmokusei|ja|キンモクセイ|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kinmokusei|qq=}} trees. He also donated land to the shrine.{{Sfn|Gunma Cultural Affairs Department|2022|pp=350-354}}

The shrine is famous for its {{ill|Boke (Chaenomeles)|ja|ボケ|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Boke (Chaenomeles)|qq=}} flowers, designated as a natural monument by Gunma Prefecture.

