* {{ill|Yakushi Nyorai|ja|薬師菩薩明神|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Yakushi Nyorai|qq=}}

== Overview ==

The shrine is said to have been founded in [[:en:1125|1125]] ({{ill|Tenji 2|ja|天治2年|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Tenji 2|qq=}}) by [[:en:Minamoto no Yoshikuni|Minamoto no Yoshikuni]].{{Sfn|Gunma Cultural Affairs Department|2022|pp=350-354}}

In [[:en:1174|1174]] ({{ill|Jōan 4|ja|承安4年|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Jōan 4|qq=}}), [[:en:Minamoto no Yoshitsune|Minamoto no Yoshitsune]] is believed to have enshrined a divided spirit from [[:en:Fushimi Inari-taisha|Fushimi Inari Taisha]] in his crown upon learning of the shrine's Minamoto lineage, thus bestowing its name.{{Sfn|Gunma Cultural Affairs Department|2022|pp=350-354}}{{Sfn|Ota City|1985|pp=681-682}}

In [[:en:1333|1333]] ({{ill|Genkō 3|ja|元弘3年|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Genkō 3|qq=}}), [[:en:Nitta Yoshisada|Nitta Yoshisada]] prayed for victory at the shrine before launching his campaign. After his victory, he dedicated a ceremonial lion offering and planted fragrant {{ill|Kinmokusei|ja|キンモクセイ|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kinmokusei|qq=}} trees. He also donated land to the shrine.{{Sfn|Gunma Cultural Affairs Department|2022|pp=350-354}}

The shrine is famous for its {{ill|Boke (Chaenomeles)|ja|ボケ|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Boke (Chaenomeles)|qq=}} flowers, designated as a natural monument by Gunma Prefecture.

