'''Kanmuri Inari Shrine''' (冠稲荷神社) is a [[:en:Shinto shrine|Shinto shrine]] located in {{ill|Hosoya|ja|細谷町|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Hosoya|qq=}}, Ota City, Gunma Prefecture. It is regarded as one of the {{ill|Seven Great Inari Shrines|ja|日本七社|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Seven Great Inari Shrines|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to 稲荷神}}.<ref>{{Cite web|ja|title=冠稲荷神社と日本七社|url=https://kanmuri.com/ka/jinjanituite/kannmuri_nanansya/|publisher=Kanmuri Inari Shrine|accessdate=2024-11-26}}</ref> Historically, the shrine was revered as a deity of sericulture. It is classified as a former {{ill|Sonsha|ja|村社|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Sonsha|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to 近代社格制度}} under Japan's modern shrine Ranking system.{{Sfn|Ota City|1985|pp=42,57-58}}

== Enshrined Deities ==

* {{ill|Ukanomitama|lt=Uka-no-Mitama-no-Kami|ja|宇迦御魂神|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ukanomitama|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to ウカノミタマ}}
* {{ill|Ōnamuchi-no-Mikoto|ja|大穴牟遅神|1=Ōkuninushi|lt=Ōnamuchi|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ōnamuchi-no-Mikoto|13=User:Immanuelle/Ōkuninushi|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to 大国主}}
* {{ill|Ōta-no-Mikoto|lt=Ōta-no-Mikoto|lt=Ōta-no-Kami|ja|太田神|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ōta-no-Kami|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to 太田命}}
* {{ill|Ōmiya-no-Me|lt=Ōmiya-no-Me|lt=Ōmiyahime-no-Mikoto|ja|大宮能売神|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ōmiyahime-no-Mikoto|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to オオミヤノメ}}
* {{ill|Ukemochi|ja|保食命|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ukemochi|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to 保食神}}
