== Cultural Properties ==

=== Gunma Prefectural Cultural Properties ===

'''Important Cultural Properties:'''
* Main Hall and Seitengū Shrine (Designated September 26, 1972)<ref>{{Cite web|ja|title=冠稲荷神社の本殿並びに聖天宮|url=https://www.city.ota.gunma.jp/page/4399.html|publisher=Ota City|accessdate=2024-08-23}}</ref>
''' Main Hall: Built in [[:en:1767|1767]], featuring three-bay [[:en:Nagare-zukuri|Nagare-zukuri]] with Chidori gable and Karahafu porch.
''' Seitengū Shrine: Four-sided [[:en:East Asian hip-and-gable roof|Irimoya-zukuri]] with Karahafu roof, built in [[:en:1857|1857]].{{Sfn|Gunma Cultural Affairs Department|2022|pp=350-354}}<ref name=":0">{{Cite web|ja|title=冠稲荷神社を県重文に答申|url=https://www.jomo-news.co.jp/articles/-/507830|publisher=Jomo Shimbun|accessdate=2024-08-02}}</ref>

'''Natural Monuments:'''
* {{ill|Boke (Chaenomeles)|ja|ボケ|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Boke (Chaenomeles)|qq=}} Trees (Designated January 14, 1955)<ref>{{Cite web|ja|title=冠稲荷のボケ|url=https://www.city.ota.gunma.jp/page/4397.html|publisher=Ota City|accessdate=2024-08-23}}</ref>
''' Estimated to be 300–400 years old, forming dense clusters over a semicircular area. Flowers bloom in mid-March to early April.

=== Ota City Designated Cultural Properties ===

'''Intangible Cultural Properties:'''
* Hosoya Kanmuri Inari Lion Dance (Designated March 25, 1994)<ref>{{Cite web|ja|title=細谷冠稲荷の獅子舞|url=https://www.city.ota.gunma.jp/page/4496.html|publisher=Ota City|accessdate=2024-08-23}}</ref>
''' Associated with Nitta Yoshisada's ceremonial lion offering. Performed during the {{ill|Hatsuo|ja|初午|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Hatsuo|qq=}} Grand Festival.

