'''Kanmuri Inari Shrine''' (冠稲荷神社) is a [[:en:Shinto shrine|Shinto shrine]] located in {{ill|Hosoya|ja|細谷町|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Hosoya|qq=|1=Hosoya|comment=changed title based on wikidata|WD=Q27501215}}, Ota City, Gunma Prefecture. It is regarded as one of the {{ill|Seven Great Inari Shrines|ja|日本七社|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Seven Great Inari Shrines|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to 稲荷神|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to 稲荷神|1=Inari|comment=changed title based on wikidata|WD=Q719665}}.<ref>{{Cite web|ja|title=冠稲荷神社と日本七社|url=https://kanmuri.com/ka/jinjanituite/kannmuri_nanansya/|publisher=Kanmuri Inari Shrine|accessdate=2024-11-26}}</ref> Historically, the shrine was revered as a deity of sericulture. It is classified as a former {{ill|Sonsha|ja|村社|lt=Son-sha|1=modern system of ranked Shinto shrines|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Sonsha|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to 近代社格制度|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to 近代社格制度|comment=changed title based on wikidata|WD=Q712534}} under Japan's modern shrine Ranking system.{{Sfn|Ota City|1985|pp=42,57-58}}

