== Overview ==

The shrine is said to have been founded in {{ill|1125|en|1125|qid=Q23799|lt=1125|1=1125}} ({{ill|Tenji 2|ja|天治2年|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Tenji 2|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid|qid=Q135579683|1=1125}}) by {{ill|Minamoto no Yoshikuni|en|Minamoto no Yoshikuni|qid=Q3314719|lt=Minamoto no Yoshikuni|1=Minamoto no Yoshikuni}}.{{Sfn|Gunma Cultural Affairs Department|2022|pp=350-354}}

In {{ill|1174|en|1174|qid=Q19690|lt=1174|1=1174}} ({{ill|Jōan 4|ja|承安4年|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Jōan 4|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid|qid=Q135579684|1=1174}}), {{ill|Minamoto no Yoshitsune|en|Minamoto no Yoshitsune|qid=Q310445|lt=Minamoto no Yoshitsune|1=Minamoto no Yoshitsune}} is believed to have enshrined a divided spirit from {{ill|Fushimi Inari-taisha|en|Fushimi Inari-taisha|qid=Q714828|lt=Fushimi Inari Taisha|1=Fushimi Inari-taisha}} in his crown upon learning of the shrine's Minamoto lineage, thus bestowing its name.{{Sfn|Gunma Cultural Affairs Department|2022|pp=350-354}}{{Sfn|Ota City|1985|pp=681-682}}

In {{ill|1333|en|1333|qid=Q6004|lt=1333|1=1333}} ({{ill|Genkō 3|ja|元弘3年|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Genkō 3|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid|qid=Q135579685|1=1333}}), {{ill|Nitta Yoshisada|en|Nitta Yoshisada|qid=Q1328796|lt=Nitta Yoshisada|1=Nitta Yoshisada}} prayed for victory at the shrine before launching his campaign. After his victory, he dedicated a ceremonial lion offering and planted fragrant {{ill|Kinmokusei|ja|キンモクセイ|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kinmokusei|1=Osmanthus fragrans var. aurantiacus|comment=changed title based on wikidata|qid=Q11297955}} trees. He also donated land to the shrine.{{Sfn|Gunma Cultural Affairs Department|2022|pp=350-354}}

The shrine is famous for its {{ill|Boke (Chaenomeles)|ja|ボケ|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Boke (Chaenomeles)|1=Boke|comment=changed title based on wikidata|qid=Q891202}} flowers, designated as a natural monument by Gunma Prefecture.

